fields.javadoc:
If set, there is not relocation information
 in this file. This is usually clear for objects
 and set for executables.
fields.name: F_RELFLG
fields.comment:
If set, there is not relocation information
 in this file. This is usually clear for objects
 and set for executables.

fields.javadoc:
If set, all unresolved symbols have been resolved 
 and the file may be considered executable.
fields.name: F_EXEC
fields.comment:
If set, all unresolved symbols have been resolved 
 and the file may be considered executable.

fields.javadoc:
If set, all line number information has been removed
 from the file (or was never added in the first place).
fields.name: F_LNNO
fields.comment:
If set, all line number information has been removed
 from the file (or was never added in the first place).

fields.javadoc:
If set, all local symbols have been removed from 
 the file (or were never added in the first place).
fields.name: F_LSYMS
fields.comment:
If set, all local symbols have been removed from 
 the file (or were never added in the first place).

fields.javadoc: Indicates this file is a minimal object file (".m")
fields.name: F_MINMAL
fields.comment: Indicates this file is a minimal object file (".m")

fields.javadoc:
Indicates this file is a fully bound update
 file.
fields.name: F_UPDATE
fields.comment:
Indicates this file is a fully bound update
 file.

fields.javadoc:
Indicates this file has had its bytes
 swabbed (in names).
fields.name: F_SWABD
fields.comment:
Indicates this file has had its bytes
 swabbed (in names).

fields.javadoc: Indicates that the file is 32-bit little endian.
fields.name: F_AR32WR
fields.comment: Indicates that the file is 32-bit little endian.
